You are trying to access linear layout from the Button view that was passed from the onClick() listener. So Linear layout is null.

Change your click listener view param from v to view:

    dugme.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
         @Override
         public void onClick(View view) { // param now is view instead of v.
             // now you will access the real linear layout from main fragment view.
             LinearLayout linearni =(LinearLayout)v.findViewById(R.id.linearni);
         }
    });

 - First of all, you have to check the id which you have passed in LinearLayout&#39;s findViewById method &quot;linearni&quot; with the id of LinearLayout declared in frag2.xml file.

 - Second thing, you can find your LinearLayout outside the button&#39;s click event. 

Like this


    public View onCreateView(@NonNull LayoutInflater inflater, @Nullable ViewGroup container, @Nullable Bundle savedInstanceState) {
     View v = inflater.inflate(R.layout.frag2,container,false);
     LinearLayout linearni = (LinearLayout)v.findViewById(R.id.linearni);

    dugme = (Button) v.findViewById(R.id.dugme);
    dugme.setOnClickListener(new View.OnClickListener() {
        @Override
        public void onClick(View view) {
            
            Button newbtn = new Button(getActivity().getApplicationContext());
            newbtn.setLayoutParams(new LinearLayout.LayoutParams(150,150));
            newbtn.setText(&quot;Yea&quot;);
            linearni.addView(newbtn);
        }
    });
    return v;
    }

